                                                                                                               SEC ready to join the action
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Mumbai, Feb. 3: A team of officials from the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC)  the capital market regulator in the US  is arriving in Mumbai tonight to gather information on the Satyam imbroglio.        
	The SEC officials will call on the Securities and Exchange Board of India and later meet the reconstituted board of Satyam Computer Services Ltd.        
	Sources said the team would meet Sebi officers tomorrow and then proceed to Hyderabad the next day. The two regulators will also discuss a range of other general issues.        
	Sources from Sebi confirmed the meeting but refused to divulge any more details. It couldnt be ascertained whether SEC officials would assist Sebi in its investigations into the Satyam fraud.        
	On Monday, Sebi chairman C.B. Bhave had told reporters that the regulator would seek help from the SEC.         
	Satyam Computer Services floated American depositary receipts that are listed on the New York Stock Exchange. Trading on the NYSE in the Satyam ADR was suspended after B. Ramalinga Raju confessed on January 7 that he had fudged the accounts for several years.         
	Trading in the ADRs resumed on January 12.        
	US investors in Satyam have filed 12 class action law suits against the Hyderabad-based company in various US courts. Satyam has appointed counsel to defend itself.        
	Last week, the SEC said it had not yet taken any disciplinary action against the software giant. However, it hasnt ruled out regulatory and enforcement steps to protect Satyams investors.        
	Board meet        
	The two-day Satyam board meeting beginning tomorrow will consider 6-7 buyout offers and discuss the Rs 600-700 crore short-term funding requirements to be provided by three public sector banks.                                                                                                                                        
